1
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:04,333
I'm glad that we can all attend
Tonan University.

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:06,733
Congratulations.

3
00:00:06,900 --> 00:00:10,167
If you go to Tokyo University,
your parents will be proud of you.

4
00:00:10,333 --> 00:00:13,733
You've only brought me troubles.

5
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:17,167
-Are you okay?
-How about your entrance exam?

6
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:18,367
I didn't take it.

7
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:23,000
I'm really sorry.
Because of my daughter,

8
00:00:23,167 --> 00:00:25,100
your precious son had to ruin his future.

9
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:28,833
Let me be clear. It's not your fault that
I didn't take the entrance exam.

10
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:33,133
I felt that it would be nice for me
to go to Tonan with others.

11
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:37,167
You mean you want to go
to the college with me?

12
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:41,933
That's not what I meant.

13
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:46,167
<i>After many twists and turns,</i>

14
00:00:46,967 --> 00:00:49,367
<i>Irie has decided to go to Tonan University</i>

15
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:52,400
<i>with me.</i>

16
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:55,300
<i>It's March.</i>

17
00:00:55,967 --> 00:00:59,933
<i>It's time to say goodbye to Tonan High</i>
<i>School where we spent three years.</i>

18
00:01:01,867 --> 00:01:02,833
<i>That's right.</i>

19
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,567
<i>Our graduation is getting closer.</i>

20
00:01:05,733 --> 00:01:06,767
8 DAYS TO GRADUATION CEREMONY

21
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:10,500
You have only eight days
until the graduation ceremony.

22
00:01:11,467 --> 00:01:15,100
Soon you have to say goodbye
to your friends,

23
00:01:15,433 --> 00:01:17,967
with whom you spent three years together.

24
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:21,700
What's wrong? C'mon. Cheer up.

25
00:01:23,267 --> 00:01:26,000
Hey, what's the matter?
Hello, Class F?

26
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:34,600
Finally we all know which university
we are attending.

27
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:39,000
Many in this class do not go to Tonan,
unlike other classes.

28
00:01:39,067 --> 00:01:41,300
I will miss you all.

29
00:01:42,467 --> 00:01:46,100
Many? Tell the truth.
I'm the only one to stay with Tonan.

30
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:50,900
That's true.
I don't mean to make you feel bad.

31
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:53,500
Are you really sure about your choice?

32
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:57,800
If I really want to go to Tokyo
University, I can try again next year.

33
00:01:59,067 --> 00:02:00,733
That's right.

34
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:03,767
I'm sure that you will be accepted
if you apply.

35
00:02:04,967 --> 00:02:08,233
Watanabe, Waseda is your first choice.
Congratulations.

36
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,333
Thank you.

37
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:16,033
Irie is really staying with Tonan.

38
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:18,233
I'm shocked.

39
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:22,900
I've heard that he missed the entrance
exam of Tokyo University on purpose.

40
00:02:22,967 --> 00:02:23,900
Why?

41
00:02:25,067 --> 00:02:28,267
Don't tell me that it's because the girl
in Class F goes to Tonan.

42
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:33,233
Soon we will be a high school graduate.

43
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:36,733
Kotoko, you must make special memories
with Irie before the graduation.

44
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:40,900
Not really. We are going
to the same college anyway.

45
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:43,700
What's wrong with you?
Our high school life will be over soon.

46
00:02:43,867 --> 00:02:46,867
It's a perfect time to get closer to him.

47
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:50,933
Irie goes to Tonan,
because she goes there.

48
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:52,633
Everyone is guessing so.

49
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,233
I can't believe it.

50
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,400
What is he thinking?

51
00:02:56,567 --> 00:02:59,633
You two get together at the graduation.

52
00:03:01,567 --> 00:03:03,667
I'm blushing.

53
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:07,500
At least you should get a kiss.

54
00:03:07,667 --> 00:03:08,867
That's good.

55
00:03:09,033 --> 00:03:10,433
To commemorate the graduation,

56
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,733
you should have the first kiss.

57
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:16,600
Stop it. It is not going to happen.

58
00:03:16,767 --> 00:03:20,067
Do you know a legend of this school?

59
00:03:20,233 --> 00:03:25,667
A couple who kisses on the
graduation day stays together forever.

60
00:03:25,967 --> 00:03:28,233
-Really?
-I've heard about that.

61
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:33,167
But I don't know if Kotoko has a chance.

62
00:03:34,867 --> 00:03:37,133
You may be right.

63
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,733
You may be right. A kiss?

64
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:42,700
The first

65
00:03:42,867 --> 00:03:44,233
kiss?

66
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,133
<i>It is</i>

67
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:51,433
<i>a special kiss which you can experience</i>

68
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:53,733
<i>only once in your life.</i>

69
00:03:54,533 --> 00:03:57,900
<i>I have been longing</i>

70
00:03:58,067 --> 00:04:00,467
<i>for the first kiss for a long time.</i>

71
00:04:00,933 --> 00:04:02,967
<i>But I didn't expect</i>

72
00:04:03,133 --> 00:04:05,300
<i>that it would happen in that way.</i>

73
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:10,367
MISCHIEVOUS KISS

74
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:13,133
{\an8}-What do you wear for a graduation party?
-A suit jacket or jeans?

75
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,833
{\an8}WHO WILL GET THE FIRST KISS!?

76
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:18,433
{\an8}Three of you are organizers of this party,
huh?

77
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,800
{\an8}That's right.
We haven't picked the venue yet.

78
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,967
But we really want you to come.

79
00:06:23,133 --> 00:06:25,067
Of course I will.

80
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:27,467
All of you studied so hard.
I'm proud of you.

81
00:06:27,633 --> 00:06:29,833
I really congratulate you
on your graduation.

82
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:30,900
Thanks.

83
00:06:31,067 --> 00:06:35,667
We are so glad that everyone
of Class F was able to graduate.

84
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:38,900
We will make our party the best.
Right, teacher?

85
00:06:39,067 --> 00:06:40,600
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

86
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:42,267
But a student doesn't

87
00:06:42,433 --> 00:06:46,867
want to attend the graduation ceremony.

88
00:06:47,033 --> 00:06:48,067
What?

89
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,600
Didn't you hear

90
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:54,267
about Kinnosuke Ikezawa?

91
00:06:55,467 --> 00:06:57,433
Kin-chan?

92
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,567
Now I realize

93
00:07:01,933 --> 00:07:04,833
that he is absent today.

94
00:07:06,867 --> 00:07:09,700
Are you saying that he can't graduate?

95
00:07:11,633 --> 00:07:13,800
It's possible.

96
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:15,633
He always fails...

97
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,933
Wait. He got enough units to graduate.

98
00:07:20,133 --> 00:07:22,700
He can graduate, but...

99
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,733
Hi, Kin-chan.

100
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:54,733
Kotoko. How do you find me?

101
00:07:56,167 --> 00:07:58,400
Gintaro and Dozo told me.

102
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:03,100
Idiots! They shouldn't have told you.

103
00:08:06,867 --> 00:08:07,833
Kin-chan.

104
00:08:09,067 --> 00:08:11,367
Let's attend the graduation ceremony
together.

105
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:13,833
Both Gintaro and Dozo
are so worried about you.

106
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,200
They told you everything, right?

107
00:08:25,367 --> 00:08:27,767
I got rejected by Tonan University.

108
00:08:34,567 --> 00:08:36,100
But you are not the only one

109
00:08:36,267 --> 00:08:38,500
who was rejected in our class.

110
00:08:39,867 --> 00:08:42,500
Gintaro and Dozo go
to a technical school. Right?

111
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,700
You know what?

112
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:55,867
I came to Tokyo from Osaka,

113
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:59,633
hoping to do something big.

114
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,467
Something big? Like what?

115
00:09:05,067 --> 00:09:06,333
I don't know that yet.

116
00:09:08,167 --> 00:09:11,433
But you only live once.

117
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,667
Every man would like to do something big,

118
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:17,133
to marry a perfect girl,

119
00:09:18,267 --> 00:09:19,933
and to have a perfect family.

120
00:09:22,033 --> 00:09:23,367
To accomplish these,

121
00:09:24,900 --> 00:09:27,767
I convinced myself to go
to the biggest city in Japan.

122
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:33,433
I came to Tokyo by myself.

123
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:46,567
But I failed.

124
00:09:49,133 --> 00:09:50,633
How could I compete

125
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,300
with Irie?

126
00:09:54,733 --> 00:09:55,800
Why Irie?

127
00:09:55,967 --> 00:09:57,133
You know why.

128
00:09:57,767 --> 00:10:01,833
I declared defiantly that I loved you
more than anyone.

129
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,500
But now I can't even go to a college.

130
00:10:08,133 --> 00:10:09,767
Irie gave up Tokyo University

131
00:10:09,933 --> 00:10:13,567
to attend Tonan University with you.

132
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:19,467
Not exactly.

133
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:23,200
I keep on losing to him.

134
00:10:24,967 --> 00:10:26,767
I'm disappointed by myself.

135
00:10:39,967 --> 00:10:42,367
College education
won't determine your value.

136
00:10:45,933 --> 00:10:46,833
Remember?

137
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:48,900
I'm sure I told you about this.

138
00:10:49,467 --> 00:10:52,633
My father and Irie's father
are the best friends, right?

139
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,300
Irie's father is

140
00:10:57,633 --> 00:11:00,900
a graduate of Tokyo University.

141
00:11:01,067 --> 00:11:02,333
Yeah, yeah.

142
00:11:05,733 --> 00:11:07,500
<i>He started his own business</i>

143
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:10,667
<i>and developed it into a big corporation.</i>

144
00:11:16,433 --> 00:11:19,667
On the other hand, my father didn't even
attend a high school.

145
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:27,067
<i>Right after graduating the middle school,</i>
<i>he became an apprentice to a chef.</i>

146
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,967
You know that, right?

147
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:41,133
But they like each other so much.

148
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:45,800
They respect each other's profession.

149
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:52,600
If they didn't, you guys
wouldn't have a place to live now.

150
00:11:52,767 --> 00:11:55,000
He wouldn't invite you into his house.

151
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:56,733
I know.

152
00:11:57,300 --> 00:12:00,100
What I'm trying to say is...

153
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:03,933
you and I are not good at academic stuff,

154
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:08,867
but we can find something we are good at.

155
00:12:11,167 --> 00:12:13,467
Something I'm good at?

156
00:12:15,367 --> 00:12:18,900
Find something big, something that only
you can accomplish.

157
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:26,000
Hey.

158
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:31,000
If I find it and become successful,

159
00:12:31,767 --> 00:12:34,000
will you fall in love with me?

160
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:38,333
Well, that's another issue.

161
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,733
Well...

162
00:12:44,533 --> 00:12:46,433
As Irie said, nobody knows

163
00:12:47,833 --> 00:12:49,667
what will happen next.

164
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:54,933
"I don't like her today,
but I may like her tomorrow."

165
00:12:56,633 --> 00:12:59,667
I don't mean that I dislike you.

166
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:04,633
You are my friend. That's all.

167
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,700
That's fine for now.

168
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:11,633
I will find something I'm good at

169
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:15,867
and become the best of it.

170
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:20,433
Kotoko, wait for me until then.

171
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,900
Will you come
to the graduation ceremony?

172
00:13:23,067 --> 00:13:24,133
Okay.

173
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,100
I will attend it with head held high.

174
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:31,567
Grades do not determine my value.

175
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:37,367
I won't lose to Irie, no matter what.
I will be a big shot.

176
00:13:38,733 --> 00:13:41,000
Let's make the graduation ceremony
great together.

177
00:13:41,167 --> 00:13:44,733
-Okay. Let's make great memories.
-Yes.

178
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,733
Miss, what can I get for you?

179
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:49,033
Well...

180
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,200
Let's see...

181
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:54,200
Mandhe...ling?

182
00:13:54,367 --> 00:13:55,633
Sure.

183
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,333
It's called Mandheling coffee.

184
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:04,267
-Kotoko.
-Yes?

185
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:08,200
What's that?

186
00:14:08,367 --> 00:14:10,067
I will miss you.

187
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:12,333
I will miss you, too.

188
00:14:12,633 --> 00:14:16,467
I will miss you, but we have to move on.

189
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,867
Hey!

190
00:14:25,467 --> 00:14:27,633
Kin-chan is back.

191
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:28,900
Bro!

192
00:14:29,067 --> 00:14:30,200
Kin-chan, have you gotten over it?

193
00:14:30,367 --> 00:14:32,233
-"Gotten over it"? What do you mean?
-About college.

194
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,033
Jinko, shut your mouth.

195
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,300
No, no, no.

196
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:40,333
I've decided to become a man
earlier than you can.

197
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:41,733
And I will be ready for...

198
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:43,033
C'mon, Kotoko.

199
00:14:46,033 --> 00:14:47,600
That's my goal.

200
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:50,900
I got it. Instead of going to a college,
he will get a job.

201
00:14:51,067 --> 00:14:53,267
Kin-chan, you are very positive.

202
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:56,833
Or I would say "happy-go-lucky."

203
00:14:57,833 --> 00:15:01,267
I'm glad to see you in the graduation
ceremony with us.

204
00:15:01,433 --> 00:15:03,533
Thanks. By the way,

205
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:05,567
you are the organizers of the party,
right?

206
00:15:05,733 --> 00:15:09,733
That's right. Jinko and I were just
debating which restaurant we should pick.

207
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:13,100
Our budget is very small,
so we don't have many options.

208
00:15:16,667 --> 00:15:20,067
Butalian? No, this place isn't good.

209
00:15:20,233 --> 00:15:22,100
I will help you organize this party.

210
00:15:22,267 --> 00:15:25,600
I will make it the best. Trust me.

211
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:27,233
What do you think?

212
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,400
Well...

213
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:33,500
We can trust your judgment
only about food.

214
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:36,400
"Only about food"?
What are you trying to say?

215
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:38,433
Kin-chan, thank you for your help.

216
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,567
Listen up, everyone.

217
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,500
I will make

218
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:53,367
our last night of high school
the most memorable one.

219
00:15:54,233 --> 00:15:57,067
Just "wash your face" and wait.
I will show you.

220
00:15:57,733 --> 00:15:59,000
If you want to use the old proverb,
it is "wash your neck."

221
00:15:59,167 --> 00:16:01,067
Neck. "Wash your neck."

222
00:16:01,233 --> 00:16:02,933
Just "wash your neck" and wait.
I will show you.

223
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:05,367
Yeah!

224
00:16:06,067 --> 00:16:08,667
Let's wash our face, too.

225
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:11,167
Sure. Wash your face, too.

226
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,800
GRADUATION DAY

227
00:16:15,667 --> 00:16:18,500
You look so cute, Kotoko. Smile.

228
00:16:18,667 --> 00:16:19,933
Good.

229
00:16:21,267 --> 00:16:23,767
Give me upturned eyes.

230
00:16:23,933 --> 00:16:26,200
Imagine that the camera is my son.

231
00:16:26,367 --> 00:16:27,967
Stop it.

232
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,800
Go behind the chair.

233
00:16:30,967 --> 00:16:32,500
And do like this.

234
00:16:32,667 --> 00:16:34,733
That's right. That's right.

235
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,300
Ready? Say cheese.
So cute.

236
00:16:37,467 --> 00:16:38,533
You are so cute.

237
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:41,233
Now sit here and lean to your left.

238
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:42,767
Just like that.

239
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:45,133
Are you ready?

240
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:48,600
You are so cute. I love this shot.

241
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:52,967
This is the last day

242
00:16:53,133 --> 00:16:54,767
I can see you in the uniform.

243
00:16:55,733 --> 00:16:57,400
C'mon, Dad.

244
00:16:57,567 --> 00:16:59,067
I got enough interior shots.

245
00:16:59,233 --> 00:17:01,600
Now let's go outside.

246
00:17:02,767 --> 00:17:03,867
Good timing.

247
00:17:04,033 --> 00:17:05,867
This is a memorable day.

248
00:17:06,033 --> 00:17:09,300
Let's take a photo of you two.

249
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:20,100
He wouldn't do that, of course.

250
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:22,500
You want to take a photo or not?

251
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:27,367
Kotoko, this must be your lucky day.

252
00:17:27,533 --> 00:17:29,600
Let's go.

253
00:17:29,767 --> 00:17:31,267
I'm coming.

254
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:40,033
Are you ready?

255
00:17:40,867 --> 00:17:42,200
Get closer.

256
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:44,833
C'mon, guys.

257
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,967
Closer.

258
00:17:47,933 --> 00:17:50,800
That's it. You look great.

259
00:17:51,300 --> 00:17:53,167
You have bread crumb on your face.

260
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:49,367
Since this is the last day,
can we walk together?

261
00:19:05,433 --> 00:19:07,267
Anyway...

262
