00:37:41,933 --> 00:37:46,300
I wasn't talking about Class F.

539
00:37:46,467 --> 00:37:50,533
I guess you are very sensitive
about grades, huh? I wonder why.

540
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:56,967
That's why I don't like underachievers.

541
00:37:57,133 --> 00:38:00,900
They tend to have a victim mentality.

542
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:08,100
-What did you say?
-And to appeal to the violence.

543
00:38:09,567 --> 00:38:11,133
What? I haven't done anything violent yet.

544
00:38:12,300 --> 00:38:16,533
A verbal abuse can be prosecuted.
You know that?

545
00:38:16,767 --> 00:38:19,100
Can you guys compete against us

546
00:38:19,633 --> 00:38:21,833
in anything but the physical strength?

547
00:38:33,667 --> 00:38:35,867
-Kin-chan.
-Bro.

548
00:38:36,033 --> 00:38:37,233
Kin-chan.

549
00:38:39,733 --> 00:38:41,733
Kobayakawa, I am proud of you.

550
00:38:41,900 --> 00:38:44,333
Thank you, sir.

551
00:38:45,167 --> 00:38:48,433
I'm sorry, but all the other rooms
are booked.

552
00:38:48,600 --> 00:38:53,033
I understand, but can you do something?
This is our last night of high school.

553
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:55,667
We can't have fun in the same room
with such jerks.

554
00:38:55,833 --> 00:38:57,333
But there is nothing I can do.

555
00:38:57,500 --> 00:38:58,633
Kin-chan.

556
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:01,033
Kotoko, I'm trying to get another room.

557
00:39:01,200 --> 00:39:03,800
-I'm telling you--
-We don't need another room.

558
00:39:03,967 --> 00:39:05,633
-Let's go.
-But Kotoko...

559
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:07,333
Let's go, Kin-chan.

560
00:39:07,500 --> 00:39:10,967
The teachers just lost their cool, because
they had some alcoholic drink.

561
00:39:11,133 --> 00:39:12,667
Let's have fun together.

562
00:39:26,100 --> 00:39:27,400
You've promised me.

563
00:39:29,700 --> 00:39:32,233
We will find something we are good at.

564
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:35,100
Anything other than studying.

565
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:39,100
If you believe in that,

566
00:39:39,267 --> 00:39:44,100
you won't care whatever Class A
says about us.

567
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:08,067
You are right.

568
00:40:11,767 --> 00:40:12,700
I guess

569
00:40:14,700 --> 00:40:16,467
I lost my cool.

570
00:40:21,933 --> 00:40:24,933
Thank you for making me realize that.

571
00:40:25,167 --> 00:40:26,267
Kotoko.

572
00:40:42,933 --> 00:40:45,467
You have green dried seaweed
on your face again.

573
00:40:49,733 --> 00:40:51,233
Allow me.

574
00:40:51,400 --> 00:40:53,333
Bro...

575
00:41:07,367 --> 00:41:08,633
Naoki Irie.

576
00:41:14,933 --> 00:41:16,933
Well, I have to go back to my friends.

577
00:41:25,467 --> 00:41:27,233
What do you want, Mr. Genius?

578
00:41:28,533 --> 00:41:32,633
Did you come to check
what Kotoko and I were doing?

579
00:41:34,733 --> 00:41:37,200
Are you jealous?

580
00:41:37,367 --> 00:41:40,200
Hey, are you ignoring me? Stop.

581
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:46,100
While you are enjoying a college life,

582
00:41:46,267 --> 00:41:49,667
I will do something big
and become a big shot.

583
00:41:49,833 --> 00:41:51,767
I've promised Kotoko that I will do that.

584
00:41:52,900 --> 00:41:56,367
That would sound cool
if you were accepted to a college.

585
00:41:56,533 --> 00:41:59,000
Since you were rejected
by all the colleges,

586
00:41:59,167 --> 00:42:01,367
that sounds just sour grapes.

587
00:42:04,833 --> 00:42:07,600
That's not the only thing
I have promised Kotoko.

588
00:42:07,767 --> 00:42:10,167
Tonight I will kiss...

589
00:42:14,633 --> 00:42:16,033
I will kiss Kotoko.

590
00:42:17,333 --> 00:42:19,267
If you want to have a dream,
go to bed.

591
00:42:19,333 --> 00:42:20,567
You will see.

592
00:42:21,633 --> 00:42:26,033
Kotoko is the one who wants
to have a great celebration party.

593
00:42:27,467 --> 00:42:31,700
At the end of high school,
finally she realized

594
00:42:31,867 --> 00:42:36,300
who cared about her most.

595
00:42:38,567 --> 00:42:41,000
You are jealous now? It's too late.

596
00:42:43,767 --> 00:42:45,333
Understand, Mr. Genius?

597
00:43:07,933 --> 00:43:10,767
Attention please!

598
00:43:10,933 --> 00:43:12,933
Hello, Class A.

599
00:43:13,100 --> 00:43:15,900
Hello, Class F.

600
00:43:16,067 --> 00:43:19,433
Let's have fun together.
This is our last night of high school.

601
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:20,667
Good idea.

602
00:43:20,833 --> 00:43:23,300
Why don't we share dishes
with each other?

603
00:43:23,467 --> 00:43:25,867
Good idea. Let's do that.

604
00:43:26,033 --> 00:43:28,433
Come over here.

605
00:43:39,933 --> 00:43:42,367
Of course, you are excited.

606
00:43:42,533 --> 00:43:44,767
You've got everything you want.

607
00:43:45,400 --> 00:43:48,133
Irie cannot go to Tokyo University,

608
00:43:48,300 --> 00:43:49,900
because of you.

609
00:43:50,633 --> 00:43:54,433
Because you are dumb, you have a right
to drag someone excellent down?

610
00:43:54,600 --> 00:43:56,200
Unbelievable. You are so pathetic.

611
00:44:00,500 --> 00:44:01,967
It's not her fault.

612
00:44:06,967 --> 00:44:11,600
It's not her fault
that I don't go to Tokyo University.

613
00:44:13,133 --> 00:44:15,167
-Irie.
-What?

614
00:44:17,100 --> 00:44:20,167
-You are not a complete jerk, huh?
-It will change my view on you.

615
00:44:21,333 --> 00:44:25,533
Why on earth should I give up going to
Tokyo University, because of this one?

616
00:44:27,367 --> 00:44:30,267
"This one"?

617
00:44:34,767 --> 00:44:36,933
Are you okay, Kotoko?
Hold this for me.

618
00:44:37,100 --> 00:44:39,933
-Are you okay?
-That's right.

619
00:44:40,100 --> 00:44:42,567
A smart guy like Irie

620
00:44:42,733 --> 00:44:45,400
wouldn't be manipulated
by a nobody like her

621
00:44:45,567 --> 00:44:48,367
and wouldn't ruin his life.

622
00:44:48,900 --> 00:44:50,733
Nobody?

623
00:44:51,467 --> 00:44:52,933
That makes sense.

624
00:44:53,100 --> 00:44:56,367
Irie wouldn't fall in love
with such a dumb girl.

625
00:44:57,067 --> 00:44:59,200
I shouldn't have believed the rumor.

626
00:44:59,367 --> 00:45:01,800
"Such a dumb girl"?

627
00:45:01,967 --> 00:45:05,333
Wait a second.
How dare you call me

628
00:45:05,500 --> 00:45:09,200
"this one," "nobody" and "dumb girl."

629
00:45:09,367 --> 00:45:12,200
It's very rude. Don't you think?
It is true

630
00:45:12,567 --> 00:45:14,867
that Irie helped me.

631
00:45:15,033 --> 00:45:19,000
-I may have caused him some troubles.
-Some?

632
00:45:23,433 --> 00:45:25,000
A lot. I mean.

633
00:45:25,167 --> 00:45:27,833
-That's right.
-That's right.

634
00:45:28,100 --> 00:45:30,900
You don't need to say that.
What a cold-blooded guy!

635
00:45:31,467 --> 00:45:33,733
You like the cold-blooded guy, don't you?

636
00:45:37,500 --> 00:45:40,933
Hey, hey. It's getting too hot here.
The bottom line is that

637
00:45:41,100 --> 00:45:44,133
the power of Kotoko's love
started everything.

638
00:45:44,300 --> 00:45:45,700
Irie and Kotoko are

639
00:45:45,867 --> 00:45:48,167
meant to be together forever.

640
00:45:48,500 --> 00:45:49,600
Not a chance.

641
00:45:49,767 --> 00:45:51,867
Then how about the good-luck charm
for the standardized test?

642
00:45:52,033 --> 00:45:54,600
-What are you talking about?
-We can laugh at it now.

643
00:45:54,767 --> 00:45:59,367
Irie fell down the stairs, because
of Kotoko's handmade good-luck charm.

644
00:45:59,533 --> 00:46:02,633
Right. I remember
his walking on crutches.

645
00:46:02,800 --> 00:46:06,333
<i>He missed a train</i>
<i>and had his leads all broken.</i>

646
00:46:06,500 --> 00:46:09,333
Moreover, he couldn't eat lunch.
It caused a lot of troubles.

647
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:11,967
It's not a good-luck charm,
but a bad-luck charm.

648
00:46:12,033 --> 00:46:14,333
But my point is that
it had the power of her love.

649
00:46:14,500 --> 00:46:17,000
Just the power worked
in a opposite direction.

650
00:46:17,067 --> 00:46:18,600
Wait.

651
00:46:19,300 --> 00:46:21,967
Her house was destroyed

652
00:46:22,133 --> 00:46:24,600
just after she gave Irie her love letter.
Am I right?

653
00:46:27,533 --> 00:46:29,733
<i>Besides, Irie refused to accept it.</i>

654
00:46:29,900 --> 00:46:31,200
No, thank you.

655
00:46:31,367 --> 00:46:34,900
Wow, she is a woman
who causes a storm.

656
00:46:36,567 --> 00:46:39,833
Did you get chocolate
on St. Valentine's day?

657
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:41,967
Yes, a pathetic one.

658
00:46:42,133 --> 00:46:45,167
She also gave me a strange tool
to massage my head.

659
00:46:45,333 --> 00:46:48,467
Almost comical. You don't have
good taste for a gift, huh?

660
00:46:48,533 --> 00:46:50,733
These failure stories are so entertaining.

661
00:46:50,900 --> 00:46:53,000
Who wants to share your own one?

662
00:47:04,500 --> 00:47:07,000
Oh, no... Kotoko is breaking down.

663
00:47:09,967 --> 00:47:11,567
Kotoko?

664
00:47:12,800 --> 00:47:14,300
This is so fun.

665
00:47:14,467 --> 00:47:17,167
I love to hear failure stories.

666
00:47:25,667 --> 00:47:27,233
Fine. Now it's my turn.

667
00:47:27,400 --> 00:47:29,333
Are you prepared?

668
00:47:30,067 --> 00:47:31,100
What?

669
00:47:31,267 --> 00:47:35,200
Do you think that you have
no failure stories to be exposed?

670
00:47:35,367 --> 00:47:40,167
I've never done anything
embarrassing in my life.

671
00:47:47,500 --> 00:47:50,400
Even a genius has a weak point.

672
00:47:55,300 --> 00:47:56,367
Don't tell me...

673
00:48:08,900 --> 00:48:11,133
What is this?
Don't tell me that this is Irie?

674
00:48:11,300 --> 00:48:14,633
-He is like a girl.
-He wore a female dress.

675
00:48:24,500 --> 00:48:25,767
How did you get hold of it?

676
00:48:25,933 --> 00:48:30,033
Your mother gave me another copy
and I kept it in my wallet.

677
00:48:30,200 --> 00:48:33,233
Because it's a photo of my love
in his childhood.

678
00:48:33,733 --> 00:48:35,833
But even a 100-year romance
can turn sour,

679
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:39,333
if anyone sees this photo.

680
00:48:45,633 --> 00:48:48,133
Now you know how we feel
when you make fun of us.

681
00:48:49,933 --> 00:48:53,800
Look. Look. Oh no, it fell.

682
00:49:00,600 --> 00:49:02,100
You come with me now.

683
00:49:14,900 --> 00:49:16,000
It's time.

684
00:49:16,167 --> 00:49:17,700
Okay, guys.

685
00:49:17,867 --> 00:49:19,933
Let's do it.

686
00:49:21,900 --> 00:49:23,767
<i>Hey, hey, hey</i>

687
00:49:23,933 --> 00:49:26,167
Both Class F and Class A,

688
00:49:26,333 --> 00:49:27,967
are you having fun?

689
00:49:32,167 --> 00:49:34,967
I, Kin-chan,

690
00:49:35,200 --> 00:49:37,400
will excite you more.

691
00:49:42,033 --> 00:49:43,100
I wrote

692
00:49:44,633 --> 00:49:45,833
this song

693
00:49:46,633 --> 00:49:49,733
to dedicate to a girl whom I love.

694
00:49:56,300 --> 00:49:58,600
Now I share my love with you,

695
00:49:59,300 --> 00:50:01,333
which I have nurtured for three years.

696
00:50:03,033 --> 00:50:04,933
Now I confess.

697
00:50:05,267 --> 00:50:06,833
I love you, Kotoko.

698
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:10,633
<i>I love you</i>
<i>I love you</i>

699
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:14,100
<i>I love, love, love you</i>

700
00:50:14,267 --> 00:50:17,433
Kotoko, Kotoko, Kotoko.

701
00:50:17,600 --> 00:50:19,867
Kotoko, Kotoko, Kotoko.

702
00:50:20,933 --> 00:50:25,400
<i>Tokyo is a lonely city</i>

703
00:50:25,567 --> 00:50:27,600
<i>Really</i>

704
00:50:28,000 --> 00:50:32,467
<i>They don't look at each other</i>

705
00:50:32,633 --> 00:50:34,700
<i>Seriously</i>

706
00:50:35,533 --> 00:50:39,000
<i>But listen, Kotoko</i>

707
00:50:39,167 --> 00:50:41,800
<i>Your smile</i>

708
00:50:47,667 --> 00:50:50,600
-What do you want?
-Thank you for the mess.

709
00:50:53,300 --> 00:50:57,400
I'm not scared of you.
You are the one

710
00:50:57,567 --> 00:51:01,867
who made fun of my feelings for you
and laughed at me with others.

711
00:51:06,767 --> 00:51:09,133
<i>Do you know?</i>

712
00:51:09,300 --> 00:51:12,433
<i>I'm just glad</i>

713
00:51:13,767 --> 00:51:16,633
<i>That I met</i>

714
00:51:16,967 --> 00:51:19,600
<i>You</i>

715
00:51:21,200 --> 00:51:22,433
<i>I</i>

716
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:24,600
<i>I</i>

717
00:51:24,767 --> 00:51:28,367
<i>I</i>

718
00:51:29,567 --> 00:51:30,900
<i>Am just happy</i>

719
00:51:31,067 --> 00:51:36,233
<i>With that</i>

720
00:51:36,900 --> 00:51:38,233
Kotoko!

721
00:51:45,967 --> 00:51:47,133
I had enough.

722
00:51:53,833 --> 00:51:55,667
I won't

723
00:51:57,833 --> 00:51:59,867
love you anymore.

724
00:52:02,933 --> 00:52:04,167
Really?

725
00:52:05,533 --> 00:52:08,633
You will forget about me, huh?

726
00:52:10,500 --> 00:52:13,933
That's right. Now I know who you are.

727
00:52:15,033 --> 00:52:18,000
I will forget about you and find
a handsome boy at college.

728
00:52:18,333 --> 00:52:20,267
Go ahead. Forget about me if you can.

729
00:52:32,267 --> 00:52:33,900
Can you forget about me now?

730
00:52:39,267 --> 00:52:40,400
Kotoko.

731
00:52:40,933 --> 00:52:42,400
Am I not good enough for you?

732
00:52:46,067 --> 00:52:49,700
Kotoko, I'm a man of action.

733
00:53:03,733 --> 00:53:05,367
<i>Kiss?</i>

734
00:53:05,967 --> 00:53:08,333
<i>Is that the first kiss?</i>

735
00:53:09,500 --> 00:53:11,567
<i>Is that the first kiss in my life?</i>

736
00:53:12,067 --> 00:53:15,433
<i>Is that the kiss</i>

737
00:53:15,600 --> 00:53:17,333
<i>I have been dreaming about?</i>

738
00:53:18,833 --> 00:53:20,533
<i>Did I</i>

739
00:53:20,967 --> 00:53:22,133
<i>have a kiss</i>

740
00:53:23,433 --> 00:53:25,000
<i>with Irie?</i>

741
00:55:00,967 --> 00:55:02,533
Who is that beautiful woman?

742
00:55:02,600 --> 00:55:03,433
NEXT EPISODE

743
00:55:03,500 --> 00:55:04,533
Is she your girlfriend?

744
00:55:04,700 --> 00:55:07,033
-Hell no.
-Join the same club as Irie.

745
00:55:07,533 --> 00:55:11,200
Then you can stay with him even though
you two belong to different departments.

746
00:55:11,367 --> 00:55:12,933
Kotoko Aihara!

747
00:55:14,933 --> 00:55:17,067
If you don't take action,
that woman will take Irie.

748
00:55:17,233 --> 00:55:19,700
She is beautiful and has a great body.

749
00:55:19,867 --> 00:55:21,400
You know nothing about him, huh?

750
00:55:21,567 --> 00:55:23,633
Let's go back to a life with you
and me only.

751
00:55:23,800 --> 00:55:26,500
Can't you forget about me?

752
00:55:27,033 --> 00:55:28,600
{\an8}I don't want to see you hurt.

753
00:55:28,667 --> 00:55:30,500
{\an8}DISCLAIMER:
THIS DRAMA IS A WORK OF FICTION

